## Creating GitHub Issues

Issues are tracked in **`{{repo}}`**.

### Option 1 — AI command (OpenCode)

Use the `/create-issue` slash command in OpenCode. It will guide you through gathering title, labels, priority, and body, then create the issue via `gh`.

### Option 2 — Terminal

```bash
npx issueforge issue
```

Requires `gh` CLI authenticated (`gh auth login`). No token files needed.

